The paper proposes a neural extractive summarization model for long documents, which is a common problem in natural language processing and information retrieval. The model is evaluated on two datasets of scientific papers, Pubmed and arXiv, indicating a strong relevance to the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), information retrieval (cs.IR), and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE).
